cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with learning sentence representations from unlabelled data and involves several downstream NLP tasks that involve understanding sentence semantics. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a framework for learning representations using a classifier. Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves learning representations for natural language understanding. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the framework involves vector representations and classification, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the framework involves learning encoding functions using neural networks.
